description.narrative:
Child Protection

•	Construct 3 new Child Friendly Spaces (CFS) with WASH facilities and support 5 existing CFS.
•	Provide recreational activities for 5600 children (52% girls).  
•	Train 40 community animators on Gender Based Violence (GBV) awareness and peace building (60% women).
•	Form 3  new and improve 5 existing Child Rights Clubs (children) and train 240 girls and boys on child rights (50% girls);
•	Referral systems developed in the 3 new payams (Gakdong, Denjok and Likuangole) and improving referral systems in 2 existing payams;
•	Identify separated and unaccompanied children (girls and boys) and support/refer to child protection facility (actual numbers unknown, but at least 80% of the identified children to be supported);
•	Identify and form 3 new functioning child protection committees (adults), improve 5 existing committees (30 per committee at least 50% female) 
•	Procure and distribute 3 sets of recreational materials for the new Child Friendly Spaces, and replenish materials for existing 5 CFS

WASH

•	Drill and install one (1) solar motorized water system in Pibor centre reaching 750 beneficiaries.
•	Rehabilitate 15 existing boreholes, benefitting approximately 5,000 people 
•	Test and analyse water quality of 15 rehabilitated boreholes and one solar motorized water system.
•	Train 45 new hand pump mechanics and refresher training for 120 existing hand pump mechanics (15% female); 
•	Establish water management committees (WMC) around 15 rehabilitated boreholes and support existing 37 WMCs (6 person/ committee, 50% female);  
•	Train 60 community hygiene promoters in 3 new payams on basic hygiene promotion methodologies and simple messaging and refresher training for existing 74 hygiene promoters (70% female)
•	Provide hand pump repair tools and spare parts for 15 rehabilitated boreholes and one solar motorized system 
•	Distribute hygiene kits to 2,000  vulnerable women and girls from the IDPs and host communities;
